&lt;p&gt;Lets go ahead and add a navbar&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a good place to introduce what React calls components, all your pages will have a navbar. Why hardcode that navbar on every page? Doing that will eventually give you unnessary headacks from silly things such as typo errors. The idea behind React components is so that you write the code once and just import it in all your pages.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Create a file inside src/components/ name it Navbar.js&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You have two diffrent ways you can create this component, using a regular function&lt;/p&gt;
